    "# IDX Market Primer\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objective**: Establish foundational understanding of Indonesia Stock Exchange (IDX) mechanics, market structure, and key parameters for quantitative analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Table of Contents\n",
    "1. [Market Microstructure](#microstructure)\n",
    "2. [Key Sectors & Indices](#sectors)\n",
    "3. [Data Dictionary](#data-dict)\n",
    "4. [Volatility Regime Analysis (GARCH)](#volatility)\n",
    "5. [Correlation Matrix](#correlation)\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Market Microstructure <a id=\"microstructure\"></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Characteristics of IDX:**\n",
    "- **Trading Hours**: Monday to Thursday: 09:00 - 12:00 & 13:30 - 15:49 WIB\n",
    "- **Friday Trading**: Shortened hours (typically until ~14:30 WIB)\n",
    "- **Settlement Period**: T+2 (two business days after trade execution)\n",
    "- **Lot Size**: Standard 100 shares per lot for most stocks\n",
    "\n",
    "**Market Characteristics:**\n",
    "- High volatility due to commodity exposure (coal, palm oil, nickel)\n",
    "- Rupiah fluctuations significantly impact market performance\n",
    "- Bank Indonesia monetary policy affects liquidity and pricing\n",
    "- ASEAN/China macroeconomic spillovers influence trading behavior\n",
    "- Lower liquidity outside LQ45 blue-chip stocks\n",
    "\n",
    "**Regulatory Framework:**\n",
    "- Governed by Otoritas Jasa Keuangan (OJK)\n",
    "- Algorithmic trading permitted for retail via OJK-licensed brokers\n",
    "- No blanket HFT ban as of 2026"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Key Sectors & Indices <a id=\"sectors\"></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "**Main Sector Weights:**\n",
    "- Financials ~40% weight in Jakarta Composite Index\n",
    - Commodities (coal, palm oil, nickel)\n",
    - Consumer goods and retail sectors\n",
    "\n",
    "**Important Indices:**\n",
    "- **Jakarta Composite Index (^JKSE)**: The primary benchmark index\n",
    "- **LQ45**: Largest 45 companies by market capitalization (high liquidity focus)\n",
    "- **IDX30**: Top 30 stocks in terms of market cap and trading volume"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Data Dictionary <a id=\"data-dict\"></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "### Core Financial Data Fields\n",
    "| Field | Description |\n",
    "|-------|-------------|\n",
    "| Open | Opening price of the trading day |\n",
    "| High | Highest price during the trading day |\n",
    "| Low | Lowest price during the trading day |\n",
    "| Close | Closing price of the trading day |\n",
    "| Volume | Trading volume (number of shares traded) |\n",
    "| Dividend | Dividend payments per share |\n",
    "| Stock Split | Stock split information |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Financial Ratios\n",
    "- P/E Ratio\n",
    "- Debt-to-Equity\n",
    "- Return on Equity (ROE)\n",
    "- Earnings Per Share (EPS)\n",
    "- Market Capitalization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Volatility Regime Analysis using GARCH <a id=\"volatility\"></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "**GARCH (Generalized Autoregressive Conditional Heteroskedasticity) Model**\n",
    "- Captures time-varying volatility patterns in financial returns\n",
    "- Essential for risk management and option pricing\n",
    "- Particularly useful in emerging markets like Indonesia\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import required libraries\n",
    "import yfinance as yf\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from arch import arch_model\n",
    "from arch.__future__ import reindexing\n",
    "\n",
    "# Download sample data for volatility analysis\n",
    "tickers = ['BBCA.JK', 'TLKM.JK', '^JKSE']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get data (using past 5 years to capture multiple market regimes)\n",
    "data = yf.download(tickers, start='2019-01-01', end='2024-12-31')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate daily returns\n",
    "returns = data['Close'].pct_change().dropna()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize list to store volatility models\n",
    "models = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit GARCH(1,1) model for each ticker\n",
    "for ticker in returns.columns:\n",
    "    # Remove any NaN or infinite values\n",
    "    ret_series = returns[ticker].dropna().fillna(0)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Fit GARCH(1,1) model - standard specification\n",
    "    garch_model = arch_model(ret_series, vol='Garch', p=1, o=0, q=1, dist='Normal')\n",
    "    fitted_garch = garch_model.fit(disp='off')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    models[ticker] = fitted_garch\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display summary results\n",
    "for ticker, model in models.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"{ticker} GARCH Model Summary:\")\n",
    "    print(model.summary())\n",
    "    print('\\n' + '='*50 + '\\n')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
