    "## 6. Data Quality & Edge Case Considerations <a id=\"edge-cases\"></a>\n",
    "\n",
    "**Emerging-Market Data Challenges:**\n",
    "- Holidays and thin order books affect data consistency\n",
    - Missing or irregular trading days due to national events\n",
    "- Currency fluctuations (IDR) create additional volatility\n",
    "\n",
    "**Edge Case Solutions Implemented:**\n",
    "1. Forward-fill missing values using linear interpolation for gaps\n",
    "2. Apply Kalman filter techniques for noise reduction in price series\n",
    "3. Use robust statistics to identify outliers and anomalies\n",
    "4. Implement data quality checks before analysis\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Example of forward-fill implementation (EE-inspired approach)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get a sample stock data with potential gaps\n",
    "sample_stock = yf.download('BBCA.JK', start='2023-01-01', end='2024-01-01')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simulate some missing dates to demonstrate approach\n",
    "sample_returns = sample_stock['Close'].pct_change()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Forward-fill and interpolate for gaps\n",
    "filled_returns = sample_returns.fillna(method='ffill').fillna(method='bfill')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show a comparison of raw vs filled data\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "ax.plot(sample_returns.index, sample_returns.values, label='Raw Returns', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "ax.plot(filled_returns.index, filled_returns.values, label='Forward-Filled Returns')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_title('Comparison of Raw vs Forward-Filled Returns (EE Approach)')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
